events.description: Agnes of Poitou and Andrew I of Hungary meet to negotiate about the border territory of Burgenland.
events.html: • 1058 – Agnes of Poitou and Andrew I of Hungary meet to negotiate about the border territory of Burgenland.[1]

events.description: At the Battle of Fulford, Harald Hardrada defeats earls Morcar and Edwin.
events.html: • 1066 – At the Battle of Fulford, Harald Hardrada defeats earls Morcar and Edwin.[2]

events.description: Saladin begins the Siege of Jerusalem.
events.html: • 1187 – Saladin begins the Siege of Jerusalem.

events.description: The Great Prussian Uprising among the old Prussians begins against the Teutonic Knights.
events.html: • 1260 – The Great Prussian Uprising among the old Prussians begins against the Teutonic Knights.[3]

events.description: Cardinal Robert of Geneva is elected as Pope Clement VII, beginning the Papal schism.
events.html: • 1378 – Cardinal Robert of Geneva is elected as Pope Clement VII, beginning the Papal schism.

events.description: The Nankai tsunami washes away the building housing the Great Buddha at Kōtoku-in; it has been located outside ever since.
events.html: • 1498 – The Nankai tsunami washes away the building housing the Great Buddha at Kōtoku-in; it has been located outside ever since.

events.description: Ferdinand Magellan sets sail from Sanlúcar de Barrameda with about 270 men on his expedition which ultimately culminates in the first circumnavigation of the globe.
events.html: • 1519 – Ferdinand Magellan sets sail from Sanlúcar de Barrameda with about 270 men on his expedition which ultimately culminates in the first circumnavigation of the globe.

events.description: A number of conspirators in the Babington Plot are hanged, drawn and quartered.
events.html: • 1586 – A number of conspirators in the Babington Plot are hanged, drawn and quartered.[4][5][6]

events.description: The Spanish-held Dutch town of Grave capitulates to a besieging Dutch and English army under the command of Maurice of Orange.
events.html: • 1602 – The Spanish-held Dutch town of Grave capitulates to a besieging Dutch and English army under the command of Maurice of Orange.[7]

events.description: The Treaty of Ryswick is signed by France, England, Spain, the Holy Roman Empire and the Dutch Republic, ending the Nine Years' War.
events.html: • 1697 – The Treaty of Ryswick is signed by France, England, Spain, the Holy Roman Empire and the Dutch Republic, ending the Nine Years' War.

events.description: The Walking Purchase concludes, which forces the cession of 1.2 million acres (4,900 km2) of Lenape-Delaware tribal land to the Pennsylvania Colony.
events.html: • 1737 – The Walking Purchase concludes, which forces the cession of 1.2 million acres (4,900 km2) of Lenape-Delaware tribal land to the Pennsylvania Colony.

events.description: French troops stop an allied invasion of France at the Battle of Valmy.
events.html: • 1792 – French troops stop an allied invasion of France at the Battle of Valmy.[8]

events.description: The decade-long Ragamuffin War starts when rebels capture Porto Alegre in Brazil.
events.html: • 1835 – The decade-long Ragamuffin War starts when rebels capture Porto Alegre in Brazil.

events.description: Crimean War: British and French troops defeat Russians at the Battle of Alma.
events.html: • 1854 – Crimean War: British and French troops defeat Russians at the Battle of Alma.

events.description: The Indian Rebellion of 1857 ends with the recapture of Delhi by troops loyal to the East India Company.
events.html: • 1857 – The Indian Rebellion of 1857 ends with the recapture of Delhi by troops loyal to the East India Company.

events.description: The future King Edward VII of the United Kingdom begins the first visit to North America by a Prince of Wales.
events.html: • 1860 – The future King Edward VII of the United Kingdom begins the first visit to North America by a Prince of Wales.

entities.name: Edward VII of the United Kingdom

events.description: American Civil War: The Battle of Chickamauga, in northwestern Georgia, ends in a Confederate victory.
events.html: • 1863 – American Civil War: The Battle of Chickamauga, in northwestern Georgia, ends in a Confederate victory.

events.description: The Bersaglieri corps enter Rome through the Porta Pia, and complete the unification of Italy.
events.html: • 1870 – The Bersaglieri corps enter Rome through the Porta Pia, and complete the unification of Italy.

events.description: Bishop John Coleridge Patteson, first bishop of Melanesia, is martyred on Nukapu, now in the Solomon Islands.
events.html: • 1871 – Bishop John Coleridge Patteson, first bishop of Melanesia, is martyred on Nukapu, now in the Solomon Islands.

events.description: U.S. President Chester A. Arthur is sworn in upon the death of James A. Garfield the previous day.
events.html: • 1881 – U.S. President Chester A. Arthur is sworn in upon the death of James A. Garfield the previous day.[9]

events.description: Charles Duryea and his brother road-test the first American-made gasoline-powered automobile.
events.html: • 1893 – Charles Duryea and his brother road-test the first American-made gasoline-powered automobile.

events.description: The White Star Line's RMS Olympic collides with the British warship HMS Hawke.
events.html: • 1911 – The White Star Line's RMS Olympic collides with the British warship HMS Hawke.[10][11]

events.description: Irish War of Independence: British police known as "Black and Tans" burn the town of Balbriggan and kill two local men in revenge for an IRA assassination.
events.html: • 1920 – Irish War of Independence: British police known as "Black and Tans" burn the town of Balbriggan and kill two local men in revenge for an IRA assassination.[12]

events.description: The Holocaust in Lithuania: Lithuanian Nazis and local police begin a mass execution of 403 Jews in Nemenčinė.
events.html: • 1941 – The Holocaust in Lithuania: Lithuanian Nazis and local police begin a mass execution of 403 Jews in Nemenčinė.[13]

events.description: The first Cannes Film Festival is held, having been delayed for seven years due to World War II.
events.html: • 1946 – The first Cannes Film Festival is held, having been delayed for seven years due to World War II.[14]

events.description: Six days after a referendum, King Christian X of Denmark annuls the declaration of independence of the Faroe Islands.
events.html: • 1946 – Six days after a referendum, King Christian X of Denmark annuls the declaration of independence of the Faroe Islands.

events.description: The Treaty on Relations between the USSR and the GDR is signed.
events.html: • 1955 – The Treaty on Relations between the USSR and the GDR is signed.

entities.name: Treaty on Relations between the USSR and the GDR

events.description: Greek general Konstantinos Dovas becomes Prime Minister of Greece.
events.html: • 1961 – Greek general Konstantinos Dovas becomes Prime Minister of Greece.[15]

events.description: James Meredith, an African American, is temporarily barred from entering the University of Mississippi.
events.html: • 1962 – James Meredith, an African American, is temporarily barred from entering the University of Mississippi.

events.description: Following the Battle of Burki, the Indian Army captures Dograi in during the Indo-Pakistani War of 1965.
events.html: • 1965 – Following the Battle of Burki, the Indian Army captures Dograi in during the Indo-Pakistani War of 1965.

events.description: The Cunard Liner Queen Elizabeth 2 is launched in Clydebank, Scotland.
events.html: • 1967 – The Cunard Liner Queen Elizabeth 2 is launched in Clydebank, Scotland.[16]

events.description: Having weakened after making landfall in Nicaragua the previous day, Hurricane Irene regains enough strength to be renamed Hurricane Olivia, making it the first known hurricane to cross from the Atlantic Ocean into the Pacific.
events.html: • 1971 – Having weakened after making landfall in Nicaragua the previous day, Hurricane Irene regains enough strength to be renamed Hurricane Olivia, making it the first known hurricane to cross from the Atlantic Ocean into the Pacific.

events.description: Billie Jean King beats Bobby Riggs in the Battle of the Sexes tennis match at the Houston Astrodome.
events.html: • 1973 – Billie Jean King beats Bobby Riggs in the Battle of the Sexes tennis match at the Houston Astrodome.[17]

events.description: Singer Jim Croce, songwriter and musician Maury Muehleisen and four others die when their light aircraft crashes shortly after takeoff from Natchitoches Regional Airport in Louisiana.
events.html: • 1973 – Singer Jim Croce, songwriter and musician Maury Muehleisen and four others die when their light aircraft crashes shortly after takeoff from Natchitoches Regional Airport in Louisiana.[18]

events.description: Vietnam is admitted to the United Nations.
events.html: • 1977 – Vietnam is admitted to the United Nations.[19]

events.description: A French-supported coup d'état in the Central African Empire overthrows Emperor Bokassa I.
events.html: • 1979 – A French-supported coup d'état in the Central African Empire overthrows Emperor Bokassa I.[20]

events.description: NFL season: American football players in the National Football League begin a 57-day strike.
events.html: • 1982 – NFL season: American football players in the National Football League begin a 57-day strike.[21]

events.description: A suicide bomber in a car attacks the U.S. embassy in Beirut, Lebanon, killing twenty-two people.
events.html: • 1984 – A suicide bomber in a car attacks the U.S. embassy in Beirut, Lebanon, killing twenty-two people.[22]

entities.name: 1984 United States embassy annex bombing in Beirut

events.description: USAir Flight 5050 crashes into Bowery Bay during a rejected takeoff from LaGuardia Airport, killing two people.
events.html: • 1989 – USAir Flight 5050 crashes into Bowery Bay during a rejected takeoff from LaGuardia Airport, killing two people.[23]

events.description: South Ossetia declares its independence from Georgia.
events.html: • 1990 – South Ossetia declares its independence from Georgia.[24]

events.description: The United Kingdom's MI6 Secret Intelligence Service building is attacked by individuals using a Russian-built RPG-22 anti-tank missile.
events.html: • 2000 – The United Kingdom's MI6 Secret Intelligence Service building is attacked by individuals using a Russian-built RPG-22 anti-tank missile.[25]

events.description: In an address to a joint session of Congress and the American people, U.S. President George W. Bush declares a "War on Terror".
events.html: • 2001 – In an address to a joint session of Congress and the American people, U.S. President George W. Bush declares a "War on Terror".[26][27]

events.description: Civil unrest in the Maldives breaks out after a prisoner is killed by guards.
events.html: • 2003 – Civil unrest in the Maldives breaks out after a prisoner is killed by guards.[28]

events.description: Between 15,000 and 20,000 protesters march on Jena, Louisiana, United States, in support of six black youths who had been convicted of assaulting a white classmate.
events.html: • 2007 – Between 15,000 and 20,000 protesters march on Jena, Louisiana, United States, in support of six black youths who had been convicted of assaulting a white classmate.[29]

events.description: A dump truck full of explosives detonates in front of the Marriott hotel in Islamabad, Pakistan, killing 54 people and injuring 266 others.
events.html: • 2008 – A dump truck full of explosives detonates in front of the Marriott hotel in Islamabad, Pakistan, killing 54 people and injuring 266 others.[30]

events.description: The United States military ends its "don't ask, don't tell" policy, allowing gay men and women to serve openly for the first time.
events.html: • 2011 – The United States military ends its "don't ask, don't tell" policy, allowing gay men and women to serve openly for the first time.[31]

events.description: Hurricane Maria makes landfall in Puerto Rico as a powerful Category 4 hurricane, resulting in 2,975 deaths, US$90 billion in damage, and a major humanitarian crisis.
events.html: • 2017 – Hurricane Maria makes landfall in Puerto Rico as a powerful Category 4 hurricane, resulting in 2,975 deaths, US$90 billion in damage, and a major humanitarian crisis.[32][33]

events.description: At least 161 people die after a ferry capsizes close to the pier on Ukara Island in Lake Victoria, Tanzania.
events.html: • 2018 – At least 161 people die after a ferry capsizes close to the pier on Ukara Island in Lake Victoria, Tanzania.[34]

events.description: Roughly four million people, mostly students, demonstrate across the world to address climate change. Sixteen-year-old Greta Thunberg from Sweden leads the demonstration in New York City.
events.html: • 2019 – Roughly four million people, mostly students, demonstrate across the world to address climate change.[35][36] Sixteen-year-old Greta Thunberg from Sweden leads the demonstration in New York City.[37][38][39]
